The paper deals with change detection in SAR images using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning models such as PCANet and SVM suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of fuzzy clustering, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper deals with image processing and analysis, which is a common theme in information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
